This paper deals with provenance information for queries in a database context, which is a topic that falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of semirings, which is a topic in linear algebra and optimization (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new approach for annotating provenance information, which involves annotating individual values within tuples, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the semantics of queries with difference, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
